  "body": "## Summary\n\nInstalls the Sepo agent infrastructure into `augmented-mind/podcast-editing-cli` from `self-evolving/repo` source revision `8266e2429ef741e4113e64c8da2f61ab388d8008`.\n\nThis PR adds:\n\n- `.agent/` runtime, docs, scripts, TypeScript sources, tests, and package metadata\n- `.github/actions/`, `.github/prompts/`, and `.github/workflows/` agent assets\n- `.gitignore` entries for generated agent outputs:\n  - `.agent/dist/`\n  - `.agent/node_modules/`\n\nNot included by default:\n\n- no `.skills/` directories\n- no root `AGENT.md`\n- no changes to application source, README, tests, or package metadata outside `.agent` / `.github` / `.gitignore`\n\n## Install audit\n\n| Area | Target state before install | Action |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `.agent/` | absent | added from source, excluding generated/dependency directories |\n| `.github/` workflows/actions/prompts | absent | added source agent assets |\n| `.skills/` | absent | preserved absent / not copied |\n| root `AGENT.md` | absent | not copied |\n| target application files | existing Python CLI app | untouched |\n| generated agent outputs | not present | excluded and ignored |\n| agent branches | `agent/memory` and `agent/rubrics` absent | leave for post-merge initialization workflows |\n| repo secrets | `CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN` present; no variables listed | no secret values committed |\n| legacy overlapping scaffolds | none found (`.flows/`, `.claude/`, old task actions, existing agent workflows absent) | nothing removed |\n\nThe install was prepared in a clean worktree because the existing local checkout had unrelated uncommitted application changes; those changes were not touched.\n\n## Validation\n\n- [x] `git diff --check`\n- [x] `git diff --cached --check`\n- [x] `npm --prefix .agent ci`\n- [x] `npm --prefix .agent run build`\n- [x] `npm --prefix .agent test` (`376` tests passed)\n- [x] Parsed all `.github/workflows/*.yml` files with the `yaml` package (`19` workflow files)\n\nDuring validation, a small amount of upstream trailing whitespace in copied text files was normalized so the staged whitespace check passes.\n\n## Required setup before first use\n\n1. Ensure GitHub Actions are enabled for the repository.\n2. Keep at least one model provider secret configured:\n   - `CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN` is already present according to `gh secret list` at install time.\n   - `OPENAI_API_KEY` is optional if you also want OpenAI-backed runs.\n3. Choose/confirm GitHub auth. The workflows resolve auth in this order:\n   - hosted Sepo app via OIDC broker (default/easiest path)\n   - bring-your-own GitHub App via `AGENT_APP_ID` + `AGENT_APP_PRIVATE_KEY`\n   - `AGENT_PAT`\n   - fallback `github.token`\n\nUseful optional repository variables include `AGENT_HANDLE`, `AGENT_RUNS_ON`, `AGENT_ACCESS_POLICY`, `AGENT_MEMORY_POLICY`, `AGENT_RUBRICS_POLICY`, `AGENT_SESSION_BUNDLE_MODE`, and `AGENT_STATUS_LABEL_ENABLED`.\n\n## Post-merge next steps\n\nAfter merging:\n\n1. Run `Agent / Memory / Initialization` once if `agent/memory` is still absent.\n2. Run `Agent / Rubrics / Initialization` once if rubric steering is desired and `agent/rubrics` is still absent.\n3. Open a smoke-test issue or comment mentioning `@sepo-agent /answer` (or the configured `AGENT_HANDLE`).\n4. Use the ongoing memory/rubrics workflows after those branches exist.\n",
